,Recommended,254200,28268435,"Posted: 9 December, 2016",all,5Andysalive,"Its a very nice 3D version of Factorio (+minecraft). I know it isn't exactly like it, but it has just VERY strong Factorio vibes to it.  Not as complex in the long term maybe or maybe it is... (and not as polished yet) , but thats balanced out by the 1st person perspective and the 3rd dimension. That makes things much more interesting, immersive but also nicely confusing.  Walking THROUGH a messy (first) factory is a greater experience than watching it from far above.  And of course there is the 3rd dimension thing.  It goes DEEP. Setting up a little base in a huge cave 500+m underground feels good but is challenging due to the balancing issues.There isn't really a goal and target though. Maybe thats why it's going for somwhat more micromanagement.It  adds a strong Minecraft part to the thing, which makes it different to factorio.  But thats the world, the blocks, the digging (though MUCH faster) and the mining. The crafting on the other hand thankfully feels much more intuitive, much more Factorio then Minecraft(+Tekkit&co)Some balance decisions are a bit questionable. Like the first real ore smelter being so far down the research tree. You're stuck with the 1 free one for a long time and can't even move it for a long time. Also wrong choices in research can get you seriously stuck (Suit heater&Toxic filter!).Especiall since you see no tech tree. Only google tells you, what you need for what later on.Not going into too much detail but generally crafting end research gets too grindy later on. But can be adjusted by editing xml files with an text editor.Also due to all storage systems being (imho) seriously undersized, it remains despite automation, more manual and demands more micromanagement in the longer run.With the little tutorial, ingame help, trial and error and not too much google/youtube, its not too hard to figure out how things work and get something going.Once you know the basics, and (like in factorio) with the first conveyor systems and automations it gets more complex, more interesting. The first attempt will never be great. But you learn from it.But thats not a con for me if some balance is kept. Thats part of the charm of such a game! As it is in factorio.It doesnt need a longe step by step tutorial to the perfect facility for me. Although i would have appreciated the information that conveyers simply transport stuff vertically as well. Its mentioned nowhere.Thats VERY helpful to know if your miner is at -170m. Also that new torches are made automatially from coal in the inventory, when placed and don't need to be crafted with a recipe. Its literally the only item that does this and thus not expected....The world/game creating options have several parameters suiting new players. Like keep inventory on death. I can't possibly imagine doing the deep game without ""dying back home"".Maybe with much more experience.Prize wise, especially with the expensive Frozen Factory DLC (which isn't necessary for new players!), its probably worth, waiting for a sale. But if you liked factorio and look for something  kinda similar but in 3D AND can forgive a few rough edges, its really worth it (maybe at reduced prize).Just don't hit it with expectations like for a 40€ AAA game. That's silly.PS: It runs stable for me, native 21:9 support, Graphics not amazing but nice enough. Lighting at times can be annoying. But overbright pipes have been fixed in recent update. Steam workshop support (though not that much content). All is well on the technical side.Can't tell about multiplayer though. Also mods disable Achievements. Which is the single most stupid idea game devs ever came up with.PPS: There is no Steam or game option, to change language. So its only available in english.PPPS: Warning: This game is as time-eating as Factorio. Everytime you look at the clock its two hours later then you wanted to stop playing."
76561197969715965,Recommended,254200,23623074,"Posted: 17 June, 2016",all,PhearFactor,"Great game.Objective is to mine ore to be able to build faster more powerful equipment to power and mine deeper. Eventaully the game becomes a defend your base type game with waves of flying insects. The bigger your base becomes the harder the waves get. A lot of the fun is figuring out how to make your base more efficent by building more ore transports and researching new tech and then upgrading your base.Game is updated almost every 4-6 weeks for release buids of game but there are also bleedign edge builds that are updated multiple times a week.This is a great casual game. Great for kids.If you are still on the fence, watch some videos on youtube. Thye may look very complex but it really isn't too bad and the game spoon feeds you new blocks so you don't get too overwhelmed too quickly.Some of the negatives of the game is sometimes it seems you are waiting around for ore instead of doing something fun. You could always be making your mine shaft bigger but in the begining you don't know how much space you will need. There really isn't much guidance after a very short tutorial. Also, if your base gets killed, it is no big deal. It repairs itself, So there isn't a real reason to defend it. Of course that might not always be the case since the game does get updated often and there is a large DLC being created that should be out this year."
