,Not Recommended,254200,22868995,"Posted: 8 May, 2016",all,metasynthetic,"Slow, tedious, not worth your time.Does the idea of taking 6+ hours to achive even basic automation which you could accomplish in Factorio or modded Minecraft in under 30 minutes appeal to you? How about 2 hours to be able to safely explore away from your base for more than 5 minutes at a time? And that's in what this game calls easy mode - ""Casual"" mode it literally say is for people with jobs and families. (Who is the target audience, then?)Every upgrade and machine will cost more resources than it should, and perform below expectations. The game's basic generator can only function in the shallowest biomes (not enough oxygen deeper apparently), and even then it will decline to near 0% efficiency before you reach the next layer. Said layer will freeze you to death in under a minute until you build a suit upgrade... using ore from the layer below it. Everything about the gameplay feels like it's punishing the player.Apart from the mindbogglingly slow gameplay: The graphics are generally unappealing - it tries 'realistic' textures which don't look good in voxel games in my opinion, but I will acknowledge that's subjective. The surface is ugly as sin - you will never go exploring looking for a pretty place to build an outpost, because none exist. The 3d models are passable for an indie game. Animation is barebones.The sound design is decent, the effects get the job done, some of the (brief and intermittent) background music is nice.I didn't notice any bugs whatsoever, so good job on that.Much of the flavor text in item descriptions includes the author's attempts at forced humor, which I found grating.I actively played this game for about 15 hours, with several more afk idling while waiting for automation to process materials. I did my best to give this game a chance, I kept waiting for it to become fun, and it just never did.If you're one of those GregTech-type masochists out there, you might enjoy this. (I don't understand that either, but to each their own.) Anyone else, avoid."
