,Recommended,254200,28337869,"Posted: 12 December, 2016",all,KirkWS,"Ok, I love this game, it has great gameplay and a steady preogression all of the way to the end.  I am on the fence about recommending it because of how buggy it is, which I will explain later.The Good:Gameplay consists of a voxel based mining simulator with base defense elements. There is a heavy emphasis on automation with mining rigs doing nearly all of the mining.  If you are smart, it shows in the machines and networks you build. You can build incredibly complex machines to do things like assembling rockets and feeding them into your rocket launcher, or you can build the rockets and hand feed each turret's hopper.  FC inspires you to be creative out of necessity.  I bought the expansion pack three hours into the base game, 117 hours and I'm just at the front door to the expansion pack.The Bad:If you aren't smart, this is going to be a really hard game.  Some things aren't intutive and are missing, like more of things sometimes/always going north from a hopper or energy source but no big compass. Which means that some configurations only work when the machine faces a certain direction. I would also expect at least one entire base and save file to be lost due to god know what becausebugs@fortresscraft.comdidn't respond at all to my email. You will lose so much progress.  Don't make any huge works of art.  I found a way to get items from my broken base's save file so I could finish my review.  Also, you can only kill 3 types of enemies with your gun. Using your gun is a hassle. The grappling hook is so cumbersome and frustrating to use, because of how you get caught on things and dropped (down a mine shaft).  Also the BFL is completely broken or has unlisted usage requirements. And the Laser Borer kills you even when it is turned off.The verdict: Get it, there are bugs. Lots of bugs. The base I lost was a one refinery, two turbine dump.  The base I have by end game has 7 refineries and two towers of turbines. (It also has hedge mazes and a cabin.  Because it takes 30-40 minutes for the end of game weapon to charge and you have to fire it 4 times minimum to beat the base game.) In the end, the gameplay is solid. 90% of it is trying ot figure out why something isn't working. Is it the supply line? is the ore exhausted?"
76561198043268694,Recommended,254200,21598993,"Posted: 3 March, 2016",all,Nedrith,"<new review because things have changed heavily in 2 years>Highly, Highly recommended game especially if you enjoyed modded minecraft and/or Factorio.  Why?  Becauase this takes the best of both of them and puts it into a really nice game.  Developed by a really great guy who is both always improving the game and always listening and responding to comments.Since my last review on march, 2015 it would take too long to list all the items that were added.  Even since the first paid expansion, Frozen Factory, was released it would take too long to list all the things that were added to the base game for NO ADDITIONAL CHARGE.   This is free content that doesn't even require the DLC that was released after the DLC.  The entire tutorial system has been changed, a new robotics system is being worked on, induction chargers ect.  Just to give a little idea of how much the game has changed, there has been 14 content patches since my review(16 since exiting early access) each giving new quality of life features, new machines, new mechanics along with a major expansion.  Each patch has a public beta that updates every day or every few days with balance changes, bug fixes, ect.It is a game that can take as little or as long as you like.  On the easiest settings a 50 hour game is possible.  on the hardest settings alone, you are probably looking more to 200-400 hours even more with the expansion.It's a game where you can design things as simply or as complex as you like.  You can for the most part play it however you like.  Don't want to setup complex automation, it's possible to do everything without using some of the advanced stuff.  Might not be as efficient but still possible.Without a doubt if you like automating stuff, if you like to add some base defense to that automation, and if you like the thrill of going up a 400m mineshaft using a grappling hook at high speeds this is the game for you.  It's a game where in the 50-200h of playing you can always find something to do!<old review follows>Let's start by saying that this game is still being heavily developed despite being out of early access.   Some of the newer stuff doesn't have icons but besides that the game is basically 100% completable in what constitutes a pretty decent end-game that can take 50-100+ hours to get to, with additional difficulty settings for pretty good replayability.The game does a good job of combining a minecraft style sandbox with tower defense.  It takes some of the slow and annoying parts of minecraft and removes it and gives the player a lot of tools to assist them with common tasks such as building.  building 50 blocks in a straight line in survival mode is very convienent, not to mention no wait on breaking a block and protection mode from breaking multiblocks.  The grappling hook is quite fun to use and makes grappling up a verticle mining tunnel a lot of fun.  On my 4 year old computer the game runs smoothly even with a lot of stuff going on.Overall when buying this game remember some developers wait until they have everything that they can possibly do to the game done with before exiting early access, this allows them to make excuses for whatever bugs are in the game.  This developer has done a great job at leaving early access and releasing a very stable main build along with a constantly updated bleeding edge build.  The game might not be as complete as some other games that have exited early access, but it is stable, there is a lot of fun things to do, and my biggest complaint about the game is that $12 is just way too cheap.  I would of gladly paid $20-$30 for it possibly $40"
