76561198030735744,Recommended,254200,19257627,"Posted: 24 November, 2015",all,CovertGuardian,"I don't do many reviews but this quirky gem of a game has grabbed my attention.A great voxel builder. Lots of interesting systems to figure out and problem solve with.At only 30 hours in I can't speak much about the end game tower defense game.The fact that it even exists adds spice to the early game...The early game tower defense game is only required if you choose topay attention to it.  You can play hardest core where it is absolutely requiredto win every battle.  Or you can play easy ignore it and let the mobs ""kill"" youcentral core - which reboots in about 2 minutes and your are backto another hours of building...Unlike some voxel/pixel builder games, this one is about setting up a system to do the work,not grinding through the building process yourself.We build new structures, we explore, while we explore - the machines mine, refine, shape and build parts from the ore.PRO: Big world, Interesting systems, Interesting tech treeTech growth comes from an interesting combination of exploring and crafting.CON: Small team, very active development (which are pros) means thatcommunity resources like wiki's stuggle to keep up.While there is in-game help, you can only find out about topics asyou run into them, and the explanations are not complete.If you like to plan ahead you will need to scour forum postsand the guide seciton. The FAQ in the guide section is essential to understandingsome key concepts.  Other steam forum posts contain key tidbits.The lack of documentation combined with all the things you can get thesystem to do make for a steep learning curve (at 36 hours I am just gettingout of the ""early"" game.)  But puzzling out how to get what you want to happenwith all the games systems is a LOT of fun.  You have to work for your techupgrades, but they are all the more enjoyable that way."
