,Recommended,254200,34515029,Posted: 26 August,all,Skellitor301,"FortressCraft Evolved is a bit rough around the edges, but what we got so far is a fun logistical challenge.Pros:-Responsive building with a reach as far as you can see-Pretty solid research system, could use a bit of work but it's a good system as is.-Challenge for your logistical mind, having to figure out ratios and working out the best ways to bring around the resources you require and to properly process them.-Works alright on moderate end pc's, not a lot of games you find that plays like this can run at a decent FPS, this game can.-Slimes, always fun to kill-Upgrade pretty much anything from your suit, tool/weapon, even your helper bot and defensive bot.-Grappling hook, dont hate, you're just not skilled enough to use it propperly if you do. It's so much fun once you get the hang of using it, being able to fly around and swing about like you're spiderman but more badass.-Depth. Holy hell can you go deep in this world. When you start on the surface, it's jaring to understand how deep the world is beneath your feet.-Head mounted flashlight. You have no idea how needed one is when most of the game is played underground, and handheld light sources dont add much to the game. If you can see and can do stuff, that's fun, if you can only do either or, that's a hinderance. props for a head mounted light.-Multiplayer through steam, always fun to set up a game with a friend.-Build to me option. It's tedious to set down a row of 100 of something, making sure they're all pointed the right way, and you gotta do it one at a time. This game has the option to set one, walk the distance, and build off the first set block right up to you. Makes platforms, conveyor setups, and storage options much easier to set up.-Modded support. Mods always make a game better, it expands on other people's ideas for the game and it gives the player more freedom to customize the game to their liking. The modding comunity is a bit lacking but what is there is a good start.Cons:-Development is a bit slow, but it's not abandoned from what I can see.-Research as I mentioned is good but it can be improoved upon, if you dig straight down untill you die you can rack up a bunch of research easy. So while it can be easy to cheese, it also has the habbit of putting you in a standstill when you've reached as far down as you can go and you've scanned everything already.-Combat needs work, the ability to have automated defenses is a neat part of the game, but when it comes to what you can do as a player, it tends to lack until you get further into the mid game and have better gear.-Horrizontal variety. What I mean by this is you can find new stuff and biomes out in the distance, but once you've seen the first couple you've basically seen them all. It's basically a recolor of a prior aspect from a list of biome atributes.I'm sure I've left stuff out, but regardless it's a fun game dispite it's shortcomings. I reccomend this for anyone who is a fan of minecraft with a factorio twist. Ignore anyone who says this game is just one giant logistical nightmare, that's part of the game to figure out the logistics the further into the game you go, just like factorio."
