76561197980866518,Not Recommended,254200,26761682,"Posted: 23 November, 2016",all,BIRI,"Sometimes I really wish that there would be more options when reviewing, but I just can't recommend this game. Not because it's a bad one but because of the sheer amount of wasted potential which is very disappointing. The game is pretty much the work of a single dev who cares for his game and puts a lot of time and effort into the development. Unfortunately all of that falls short because of the poor execution. FortressCraft Evolved is a great example why you can't develop a game on your own after it reached a certain level of complexity and player base. The dev is no doubt a skilful coder but less talented in the other aspects of game making. FortressCraft desperately needs a texture+model artist, ui programmer, and sound designer. Right now the game is completely out of balance. The poor visuals are overcompensated with needlessly high poly models and excessive lights. The game takes advantage of the engine's most cutting edge features yet you can't turn the music off or go back to the main menu once you've started playing. Distant blocks fly in with fancy animations but the machines right in front of the player are still popping in and out regardless of the graphical settings. These and many other issues lend the game an unpolished feel and greatly hold back it's success.Off course you can find people with insane in-game hours who just love it, but you have to keep in mind that the gameplay is heavily inflated. Early game is especially slow, all you do is wait on resources. I have 200+ hours in offline play but I was afk half the time - shopping, cooking or watching TV while the ores were mined and smelted. Every attempt I made to finish the game ended with abandoning the map after 15-20 hours, I always loose interest. To make matters worse there aren't any explanations how the dev intended the machines to be used, figuring out the right setup is almost impossible, you just don't have enough information about the blocks. You have to watch countless hours of Youtube videos in order to avoid frustration. Sadly giving feedback about your issues or interacting with the community in general is not a good idea. The game is surrounded with a ring of diehard fans who are unreasonable and the developer himself can be very unprofessional.A lot of reviews are complaining about the DLC but I'm OK with it. It has one of the worst marketing I've ever seen in my life which makes it appear as another greedy cash grab attempt, but actually adds a fair amount of content for a reasonable price. It's a good way to keep the dev motivated as I still hope that my issues with the game will be addressed one day.FortressCraft Evolved could be one of the best games this genre has to offer. It could be an excellent game to introduce new players to ""blocky"" games while still challenging veteran players. Unfortunately in it's current state the game is totally unappealing. If you are a hardcore fan of the genre you will be able to overlook the numerous shortcomings otherwise stay clear, FortressCraft will yield you nothing but anger and frustration."
