,Recommended,254200,29882795,Posted: 12 February,all,Grimtongues,"Fortresscraft Evolved is similar to the major tech mods for FeedTheBeast, with an emphasis on defending your factory from waves of enemies.  The graphics in FCE are good, but you can still play with an older PC - I'm using a GTX 650 and it's fine on medium settings.  There are many features that make it easy to build large structures - cosmetic and functional.  The Frozen Factory DLC is highly recommended - it adds a significant amount of content to the game.The difficulty settings focus mostly on ""how much time do you want to grind away"", so if you are a busy person, you can still enjoy the full content of the game without ""grinding.""  The game is more about building, planning, and some exploration - it's not as action-oriented as FTB.  In fact, the monsters mostly ignore you in FCE - the monsters are all trying to attack the center of your factory.Summary:   If you enjoy tech mods for minecraft, check out Fortresscraft Evolved."
