,Recommended,254200,32713605,Posted: 23 June,all,Khadgar,"(edited review)PrefaceWhen I first started playing this game, I was annoyed by the notifications. They wouldn't stop blinking and making noise, telling me to do various things that frankly, I didn't care about handling right at that moment. It drove me up the wall to be reminded, once every second, for hours at a time, that I would ""Build a Spiderbot Base"" or whatever. Frankly, it's a horrible implementation of an otherwise OK idea. Because of these notifications, I quit playing the game and gave it a negative review out of frustration.I eventually came back to the game and ran the console command to disable the notifications/missions. This command must be run every time you start the game, and it disables ALL notifications, even helpful ones, but it solved the annoying beeping and let me enjoy the game.The GoodThe game has ok in-game documentationThe documentation includes a build-in recipe guide (think NEI / JEI from minecraft), so you can figure out what a material is used forThe machines look pretty cool. Stampers have animation of physically crushing a metal bar into a plate, for exampleGood array of world generation options, to allow people to tweak the difficulty to their liking.Nice amount of contentThe cave terrain gen is pretty nice. There are some absolutely huge cave systemsThe Not-so-goodThe surface terrain gen is bland. It's a series of hills and mountains, populated with various rocks, plants, and 'trees', which is ok, but the colors are wild and ugly. Purple, orange, yellow, green, all blending together as you travel around.The grappling hook is awkward to use. I can't really explain how awkward it is, but it has all sorts of little nonsensical quirks which make it not reliable when you need it.The in-game options menu is quite lacking. A single volume slider, for example.No ladders! It's kinda hard to travel vertically in this game sometimes, which is odd, since it's a game all about digging deep and extracting the riches of the planet. There is an elevator lift, which works pretty good, if it weren't for...The BadArbitrary gameplay restrictions!The grappling hook doesn't function properly from depth 200m to 280m, or from 450m to 650m. This is not a bug, it's intended, but not explained! Everywhere else in the game, the hook has no cooldown, and can be used effectively to slow downward descent in a vertical shaft. However, between these depths, it can only be fired once every 5 seconds, leading to a swift demise if you were counting on it to slow you from smashing into the ground. As mentioned in the above, this makes building an elevator lift a real chore. Excavate out a shaft (using the machine that does specifically this), come back later when it's finished, and plop in your elevator! ... except, you need to place the elevator at the bottom of the shaft, and you can't GET to the bottom of the shaft, because your grappling hook stops working partway down the shaft, and you just fall to your death. Why? Who knows!Coal-burning power generators don't work below the surface, due to 'lack of oxygen'. This forces you to place your base on the surface of the planet, which is ugly.Smelters don't work underground either! According to the forums I've read, this was a balance concern, because the developer thinks it's imbalanced to smelt ores right outside the mining operation, and therefore, nobody is allowed to place smelters underground! It makes no sense and basically forces the player to build everything on the surface.In my playthrough so far, this led to a lot of frustration. I would expect that if something works, it continues to work as I go onwards. I understand conveyor belts are not very efficient, but if i wanted to scale up and use dozens of them in parallel, I would think this would work! And it does, until you reach depth 200, then it stops working because it's too cold. Brr. Ok, what about these 'tubes' I've heard so much about in the crafting menu, that specifically advertise ""not effected by cold'? Oh, I can't build them till much later. I guess I have to use the one and only thing that works, the CARGO LIFT! Granted, the cargo lift is pretty cool, but why is it the only option available to me? I won't go into further nitpicky specifics about the game, but it's definitely got it's problems.All in all, I would say this game is OK. Just remember to turn off the popup notifications using the/missionscommand every time you launch the game, and it can be fun!(previous review text, for posterity)> *beep* No ore extracted in the last minute!> *beep* No ore extracted in the last minute!> *beep* No ore extracted in the last minute!> *beep* No ore extracted in the last minute!> *beep* No ore extracted in the last minute!> *beep* No ore extracted in the last minute!> *beep* No ore extracted in the last minute!> *beep* No ore extracted in the last minute!> *beep* No ore extracted in the last minute!> *beep* No ore extracted in the last minute!> *beep* No ore extracted in the last minute!> *beep* No ore extracted in the last minute!> *beep* No ore extracted in the last minute!> *beep* No ore extracted in the last minute!> *beep* No ore extracted in the last minute!> *beep* No ore extracted in the last minute!> *beep* No ore extracted in the last minute!> *beep* No ore extracted in the last minute!> *beep* No ore extracted in the last minute!> *beep* No ore extracted in the last minute!> *beep* No ore extracted in the last minute!> *beep* No ore extracted in the last minute!> *beep* No ore extracted in the last minute!> *beep* No ore extracted in the last minute!( video link -https://www.dropbox.com/s/nzikjsnyikqncg5/bleep.mp4?dl=0)HOLY♥♥♥♥♥♥ SHUT UP! I'm still new to this game, why is there this extremely annoying sound effect playing once every second? It's like, ""GEE, I HAVEN'T MINED ANY ORE IN A MINUTE, I WONDER IF I NEED A REMINDER EVERY 1 SECOND TO ALERT ME THAT I AM STILL NOT MINING ANY ORE?""Fortresscraft 