,Recommended,254200,21224423,"Posted: 14 February, 2016",all,Kaziarl,"A technically complete game that is still being worked on, it's easy to dismiss this as a ""Minecraft Clone"" due to the voxel based game world. But there are aspects of FortressCraft Evolved that blow Minecraft right out of the water (and I really like Minecraft).For one, the world size. It's massive. I have found cave systems that could contain the build height limit of Minecraft, and then some. I have tunneled straight down and have so far gone well past 7,000 meters below the surface level, while Minecraft goes from 0 to a comparatively limited 255.As for the gameplay itself, it can be very technical. You have to build a logistics and mining network to defend your base from attacks, generate power, and be very careful not to feed any near by hive minds.In terms of how long you are playing? Well... I'll admit I'm probably not the best player, but so far I've put in 112 hours and haven't reached the ""End Game"" as of yet."
,Recommended,254200,21371635,"Posted: 21 February, 2016",all,NathanHoltBeader,"This game has had me obsessed for a couple weeks, and I gather it is still being improved.  However, I'm taking a break from playing it because it is getting tedious.  First, the game puts you on a short leash because of your need to keep recharging your suit.  After a lot of research and obtaining some iron and lithium, you can set up a camp on the surface to charge your suit and Arthur (your advicea and power done), but all the goodies are underground, and it's easier to not get lost if you dig your own tunnels.  There is also a short leash because your one and only smelter can only smelt 100 ore blocks at a time, yielding 25 metal ingots each time, and there are projects you would want to do (like get ore distributed to your doorstep) that require hundreds.  I've spent most of yesterday babysiting my smelter, and doing a little exploration while it's smelting the latest hundred pack.  Expect to do a lot of gophering before you can automate anything."
