,Recommended,254200,23979269,"Posted: 1 July, 2016",all,Schnorf,"Many people seem to complain about the game being too grindy or the tutorial being not helpful because it only teaches the basic basics.Many people are apparently not playing the game in the way that this game should be played: by automating everything.The early game can be a really bad and boring grind, but only if you are either sitting at your base and waiting for your ore extractors to dig up some ore and then grab it to smelt it at your base or exploring too much too early and as result of either, not having enough automation going on, which results in slowing the game to a crawl.If you truly feel like the game is far too grindy, my advice would be to look up a tutorial or something that teaches you how to *actually* play.Oh and the latest patch brought a rather large amount of improvements to early game progression to help starting in a new world.The game itself can easily called a 3D factorio, although that would be a bit too simple - Fortresscraft has many features that allow it to be similiar and yet different, such as the world being literally infinitely deep and having massive underground caverns (which make the ones in minecraft look like caverns for ants) to explore.Overall, I can wholeheartedly recommend this game to fans of basebuilding, automation and tower defense. (The upcoming expansion will also add tower defense comparable to the Creeper World series, which is great too!)"
