76561197970711894,Recommended,254200,24172258,"Posted: 7 July, 2016",all,ddmath,"I have been submerged in the game for a number of days now. I have barely scratched the surface and yet I have about 50 hours on each of two worlds I have created. There is a lot to like here, if you like building games, you get to start from about nothing and work up from there. If you have played Factorio it is kinda like that, and not like it too. I think the research in Factoria can be a lot faster, but then I haven't really automated enough in FCE yet to know if that is true.The 3D aspect is a lot of fun, and the world shaping and stuff just eats up my time. I level hills, fill in valleys, build walls, make neat tunnels, etc. I have never played Minecraft, but my understanding is that the movement and shaping in FCE is much faster and easier. I guess it looks similar but does play very different from my understanding.All in all I have really been enjoying the challenge of finding the ore, building up enough to work to automating getting it to the surface so I can smelt it and then use it for research and more building stuff.I would recommend watching a play through or two on youtube, there are some great folks there. Even though the game has changed over time the mechanics are mainly unchanged so you get a good feel for how much there is to do and to play with!tl;dr I liked it a lot, you should get it."
76561198042288584,Not Recommended,254200,26323208,"Posted: 30 October, 2016",all,Machine Medic,"Nothing but problems.1.) Lighting:The lighting system as it is currently implemented is completely broken.  Bloom effects are amped-up through the roof while ambient/""natural"" light is nonexistent, making this a very dark game - such that it is borderline unplayable.  I cannot begin to describe how difficult it is to see anything while playing.  Reference the attached images and judge for yourself:https://www.dropbox.com/sh/esvp0oxvj0acs7v/AACsUL_dAlfPxAZReeVmVO2ea?dl=0Depicted is a subsurface coal vane about 1-2 blocks below the surface that has been exposed.  One screenshot shows the coal in natural light, the other with a flashlight directed at it on maximum power.  Also included are screenshots of various tunnels being illuminated by a flashlight on maximum power.2.) User interface:There are very few user-configurable audio or video settings.- No brightness/gamma control- No UI scale control- No key binding (must exit and change within the Unity launcher)In addition, the control scheme is extremely awkward.  It is completely alien to that of any other game, including Factorio and Minecraft.3.) Save time on shutdown:For some reason, this game implements a savefile compression system that activates after you confirm that you want to exit to desktop.  This system will operate for well over a minute before allowing the game to shut down unless you cancel it by clicking ""exit now"".4.) Sound design:The sound design in this game is a bit of a let-down.  It tries way too hard to be a blend of retro-futuristic bleeps, bloops and machine sounds, but ends up sounding more like a bunch of stock files that were tweaked in Audacity.  This is not a deal breaker by any means, but it really helps to make this game feel like a cheap one-off.  (The main menu alone contains audio elements that pop and crackle as they move around, and at least one horribly obvious 60Hz ground loop.)I cannot in good faith recommend this game to anyone.  I was very hesitant to try it based on the other negative reviews below, but I purchased it for ~$12 w/ DLC nonetheless at the recommendation of a friend.  I will be refunding this title immediately.Caveat emptor.To the developer(s?):  The main problems with your game are not related to lack of features or content.  Your game isdesperatelyin need of usability refinements and technical polish.  When it comes to your UI and lighting systems: Instead of trying to defy convention at every opportunity, take a few hints from other games that have been massively successful.  In addition to everything mentioned above, focus on the little things that make a huge difference - like placing ""tutorial"" elements into dialog boxes, instead of floating them above peoples' heads or behind machines where they will never be seen.System specs for reference:2560x1440 144Hz displayGTX 980tii7 5820k32GB DDR4(All overclocked)"
