76561197976939633,Recommended,254200,20982059,"Posted: 5 February, 2016",all,MadMonkey,"""Minecraft with machines"" is what I'd say if I had to describe Fortresscraft in three words. They look similar and play similarly for the most part.However, FCE is focused on machines, rather than farming. Even in an unfinished state it has significant depth, and the blessing of a dev who is happy to listen and to incorporate ideas from the community. The game has had constant updates since I first purchased it, and I keep coming back after the major ones to replay and see all the new content.It's already great, but once finished it will be fantastic. It's very worth the purchase.*UPDATE*The latest updates have had some issues IMHO. The game is still a lot of fun, but the Frozen Factory expansion is very grindy. The only reason I've kept playing is because I can fire it up at work for 6 hours and leave it alone.There's also a distinct feeling that the developer is no trying to force players into playing a very specific way and thus destroying the freedom that made the game so great in the first place. That's his prerogative as the designer, but that doesn't make it any less disappointing.If some of the more heavy-handed tweaks are able to be turned off in the future, I'll update the review, but that doesn't seem likely. I still recommend the game, but not as wholeheartedly as before."
