76561198003815115,Recommended,254200,22891625,"Posted: 10 May, 2016",all,juscus,"FortressCraft Evolved is definitely a game that can absorb a lot of your time because of how expansive and intricate it is.  And that's a good thing!  I find myself constantly experimenting, changing, and iterating my systems to take advantage of new tech or just to maximize efficiency.  As of this writing, I have 200+ hours in game and I plan to at least tripple that.At first glance, it might look like Minecraft or Factorio.  But this game is much more than that and really isn't comparable.  This game rewards efficient, scalable design, not one-off systems.  You can do many things by hand, but eventually, everything must become automated.  And that is a good way to understand the game.  You must automate everything.For the price, this game is definitely worth it.  I've spent more on games that I've played less.  Additionally, the planned expansions sound exciting and definitely something I will want to play.My recommendation: if you like designing or building systems, this game is a must-have.Quick update: I'm now well over 400 hrs in game and still loving it.  The developer continues to add to and improve the game with more great features.  This is a fantastic game."
