,Recommended,254200,33892358,Posted: 29 July,all,Sweetly Sick,"It took me a couple of attempts to get into this game, and I'm so glad I persisted.  Unlike MineCraft which you can typically tame within a couple of day-night cycles, this has a much more extensive tech progression system, forcing you deeper and deeper within the world of FC to find elusive materials to take that next major step.  Think 3D factorio and you won't be far off.The survival part is fairly basic, just holding off waves of flying surface-dwelling creatures.  The hardest part about that is keeping your base sufficiently powered to keep the guns firing, easier said than done when your tech levels are low, but trivial later in the game.  The only threats in the deep are your stupidity if you fall too far, or run out of power and freeze to death in the dark.  There's no random mobs to contend with.The game is quite confusing and slow-going at the start, but that's part of the challenge too.  Keep a browser open to search for tips, some Wiki sites are very helpful.  I definitely recommend the workshop mods.A solid 7 out of 10, if you have patience.  I just hope you don't mind psychedelic colours and near invisible crosshairs!ps. If your framerate is crawling, look for alternate ways to achieve the same thing with less parts.  I had my i7 6700K with 1080ti crawling at 15fps until I replaced my massive coal-burning power plants with a few solar plants."
