76561198056807293,Recommended,254200,27330874,"Posted: 24 November, 2016",all,Superguru,For me this is one of the games that I can play for a very long time.But be warned that this game is not for everyone as it is complex and takes time.Time for gathering resources depends on world difficulty and can range from fast to taking forever.Base building time is not so much affected by difficulty (once you have the resources) but takes some thought to have a good layout. You can even screw up without knowing until it is too late. For example when you do not protect your conveyor belts and have uncontrolled hive mind growth.So before starting I recommend to read some guides and/or the wiki. If you are not willing to read then you may have a hard time. The tutorial is very basic and the ingame help is not enough to understand everything in the game. There are no scenarios or extended tutorials that show you how to master the game.Once you know how things work out it is really enjoyable to build up your base and to automate the tedious processes.The frozen factory expansion is not required immediately for this because it extends the late game. Have played over 100 hours and just about to begin with the additional content. For that amount of playtime it is well worth it in my opinion.The user interface is the part of the game that needs the most improvements. It makes some tasks more complicated than they should be. If you are deterred by this fact then better wait for improvements. It already improved over time but still needs more time.My recommendation:If you are looking for a complex game that requires time or already played minecraft with technical mods like industrialcraft (especially if you like Gregtech) then this is likely a game for you.If you are looking for a game with less complexity and quicker progress you should look into Factorio first and come back once you need more ;)
