76561198155413701,Recommended,254200,28480302,"Posted: 19 December, 2016",all,Turnovus,"FortressCraft Evolved is a game that takes place in the distant future. You start out ina cinematic event, in which you haplessly attempt to dock your personal spaceship into a space station, only to be ejected by a meteor impact, and to crash ona terrible, freezing planet. At first progression is slow. You will likely need to cling to your Central Power Hub (CPH) to power your suit, or suffer a hypothermic death. Before long, you will likely set up automated means of collecting ores and smelting them into bars. There is a ladder to progression in the sense that you must set up automated mines for new tiers of ores, set up logistics to get the ore back to the base, create machines to assemble devices, and eventually upgrade you suit to go deeper and discover newer ores. However, spread out across the planet, are creatures called hiveminds. They are encased in a thick, resinous shell that can only be destroyed with high-tier explosives/machinary. After a while, the hiveminds will become a problem, as they will spawn 'mynoks' (cis) on top of your conveyer belts, which will eat passing materials. This causes the hivemind's shell to grow, until it reaches/destroys your CPH. As well as that, there are swarms of wasps that will attack your base on the surface, and will attempt to shoot acid at your CPH to destroy it. The penalties of the CPH's destruction vary from losing the CPH's power to losing the game, depending on the world's difficulty setting. There are, however, a few ways to stop this:Using your space-aged ray-gun, powered by your suitSetting up automated turrets, powered by power cellsSetting up an ARTHER turret, a simple turret powered by power cells and controlled by your companion drone, ARTHERCharging/Arming the giant spider robot that patrols your base (this only works for surface attacks)Anyway, that's about the gist of this game. If you decide to give it a try, then have fun, good luck, and happy digging!"
