76561198062962411,Recommended,254200,29816598,Posted: 9 February,all,mattkeogh,"To anyone who isn't sure about this game it's like a 3D Factorio, However this is only a comparison to understand the gameplay and not a comparison of quality or content. If this next sentence is a pun please pardon it. The fact Fortress Craft is 3d adds so much more depth to the game. I will warn you, this game is difficult to begin with but new ""missions"" guide you through the basics without actually feeling like someone is holding your hand. In my personal experience I tried to play this game and honestly I got stuck and frustrated I was trying to be reserved instead I should think big.Your save file can be created with a special mode that enables gameplay to go by a bit quicker, but even still the complexity of this game allows for so much time to be spent. Sometimes you might think, ""Is the end"",  ""have a I finished it"" and I can promise you that you'll probably stumble upon something that unlocks a whole new chapter of gameplay.I personally think it is well worth the money and as a side note the Dev are brilliant a few times I've posted on their forums about ingame queries and about 90% of those posts get a response from a Dev. The dev are always releasing bug fixes that have been brought to their attention from the players.This game is fantastic as it is but I can't wait to see what wonderous things happen in the future. Move over Minecraft FTB."
