,Recommended,254200,31497439,Posted: 1 May,all,King Sans,"So I've had Fortresscraft Evolved for a while now and finally decided to write a review. Overall I think FortressCraft Evovled is a great game for people who have the time to sit down for a few hours and play. It combines the addicting factors of base building games with three dimensional mechanics. However that doesn't mean the game is without fault. I wouldn't reccomend playing on a mac as the overall quality of the game decreases. If you are looking for a fast paced game or one that you could sit down for 10 minutes a day and play then this is not your game. In my personal opinion the early game is very tedious until you set up copper and tin automation and even then its still a lot of finding ores, scanning, doing research, etc. Overall, if you are looking for a faster pace game with minimal grinding then this is not for you, however if you are looking for an indepth base building and automation game where there is no best way to do it you found your game."
