76561198016614899,Not Recommended,254200,29209366,Posted: 12 January,all,Artritus,"Edit: After a developer reply on how to fix the crashes this runs smootly now (it never crashed since 2 hours at least). So i edited this to reflect more about my experience.However i still leave this review as negative, mostly since there is no ""neutral"" button, and since positive would not reflect what I exerienced / felt, while playing it.I must admit, that I havent progressed further than starting some basic automation.The UI get's in my way too often, and the tutorial is minimal, not explaining you lot's of things.Geting into automation is way too tedious at start.There is some weird sound problems for me too, like if i scan down there in a hallway the shrieking echoes forewer, having me to turn down the sound to an allmost absolute minimum.While the idea might be nice, the 3 dimensions just make it horrible for me personally, since the grappling hook probably needs hours of training to make you go up and down a mining shaft without dying every second time (after another two hours i found that shooting it repeatedly towards the wall while ""falling"" down a shaft you can actually land...). Digging deep and then bringing those materials back (automated, not running down there every 5 minutes) is a pain at the start too.The idea of needing unidentified blocks to scan for research is in my eyes not really good game design. An increased amount of ore or other resources per research would be much more apropriate (or did i not progress far enough still?).One of the things that hinder me most is the limited energy at start. Just because of this, and for no other reason i run forth and back 10 or more times to just set up a mine and build the conveyors and energy supply for it. While it could be fun to dig it, find a way for the belts and the energy transmition it gets dull, because 50% of the time is ""running forth and back for energy"".Some things are really nice in there too. Like 