,Not Recommended,254200,29305202,Posted: 16 January,all,Techbane,"I really, really, really want to like this game, and for a while as I was starting out, I did. The elevator pitch is more or less ""Factorio as recreated in Minecraft"", and the first person element really does add that much more to the exploration aspect.Unfortunately, once you've got an assembly line set up for your most basic resources, the entire game's progression of tech trees turns out to be deliberately balanced a step or two behind parity with your current progress, such that you arealwayssticking your neck out, collecting stuff manually, and being forced to stretch your current equipment to its absolute limits to gather the new resource for the next tier of equipment, at which point the process repeats itself. It's less a game about automation as it is a never-ending masocore scavenger hunt. Which is a damn shame, because if just a bit more common sense were applied to the tech trees it'd be another masterpiece of the ""explore, collect, build"" genre. You still might be able to get something out of it, but I would advise caution. It's more nefarious than it looks."
